content.AccountBalanceFE:
- From my Investments 
&lt;br /&gt;
This is the estimated pre-tax monthly income, in today&#39;s dollars, which you could receive in retirement for assets earmarked for retirement (employer retirement account, other assets you may have entered).

content.OtherIncomeNonFE:
- From Other Income 
&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
My estimated income from any additional sources entered.

content.AccountBalanceNonFE_HoverTextGuaranteedI:
- From Secure Income
&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
This is from your secure income accumulated and/or projected to date.

content.LoanBankingInformationFE_BankingInfoText:
You do not have banking information on file. ACH must be setup prior to requesting a loan.
&lt;br /&gt;
Loans must be repaid via automatic deduction from your bank account each month.

content.PensionFE:
- From My Retirement Income Sources
&lt;br /&gt;
This is the estimated pre-tax monthly retirement income, adjusted for today’s dollars, which you could receive from all known retirement sources. Pension values in your dollar bill are also expressed in today’s dollars and are intended to reflect estimated buying power throughout retirement.

content.SocialSecurityFE:
- From Social Security
&lt;br /&gt;
This is the estimated pre-tax monthly income, in today&#39;s dollars, which you could receive in retirement from Social Security and/or other government-related benefit. If spouse or partner information is provided, the estimate will consider both of you. 
&lt;br /&gt;
Offsets of Social Security benefits may apply to you and/or your spouse or partner.  For information about the Federal programs that might impact you and/or a spousal or partner social security benefits go to: &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.ssa.gov/planners/retire/gpo-wep.html&quot; target=_blank&gt; https://www.ssa.gov/planners/retire/gpo-wep.html&lt;/a&gt;.

content.LoanBankingInformationNonFE_BankingInfoT:
You do not have banking information on file. ACH must be setup prior to requesting a loan.
&lt;br /&gt;
Loans must be repaid via automatic deduction from your bank account each month.

