content.PensionNonFE_PensionByAge:
- From My Pension
&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
This is based on what is entered under “Pension Income”. Changing the retirement age will adjust the model for my pension estimate.

content.SpecialNeeds_SNAdditionalBenefitsBodyTex:
An adult disabled before age 22 may be eligible for child&#39;s benefits when a parent starts receiving retirement or disability benefits. SSA considers this a &quot;child&#39;s&quot; benefit because it is paid on a parent&#39;s Social Security earnings record.
&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
The benefit below assumes 50% of your benefit. If the other parent is the higher wage earner, visit &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.ssa.gov/myaccount/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;ssa.gov&lt;/a&gt; to determine their benefit and enter 50% of their amount in the box below.

content.HowDoesThisWork_DisclaimerTextFE:
&lt;div id=&quot;faq-expand-collapse&quot;&gt;
            &lt;span class=&quot;faq-heading-title&quot;&gt;What is the purpose of myOrangeMoney&#174;?&lt;/span&gt;
            &lt;div class=&quot;ui-faq-accordion-content-visible&quot;&gt;
                &lt;span&gt;
                    myOrangeMoney is an educational interactive online experience that was created to help you get a
                    clearer picture of your monthly income needs in retirement and your current progress toward meeting
                    them and is not to be viewed as investment advice. Its interactive technology enables you to see
                    potential savings scenarios that are tailored to your personal circumstances, and supplies you with
                    the information you need that may help you to improve your retirement outlook. Whether your
                    retirement is five years away or forty, myOrangeMoney can help you understand how close you are to
                    being retirement ready.
                    &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
                    Please note that changes to your annual pay, pay increase, retirement age, pension income, and
                    income goals will be saved and used in myOrangeMoney, Online Advice and Professional Management
                    services only. These updates and changes will not be reflected in other Voya services.&lt;br /&gt;
                &lt;/span&gt;
            &lt;/div&gt;
            &lt;br /&gt;
            &lt;div id=&quot;faq-accordion-expand-holder&quot;&gt;
                &lt;button id=&quot;faq-accordion-expand-all&quot;&gt;+ Expand All Items&lt;/button&gt;
            &lt;/div&gt;
            &lt;br /&gt;
            &lt;voya-expand-collapse heading-text=&quot;Privacy&quot;&gt;
                &lt;ol id=&quot;faq-sections-inner&quot; class=&quot;no-ol-numbering&quot;&gt;
                    &lt;li&gt;
                        &lt;voya-expand-collapse
                            heading-text=&quot;Will any of the data I enter into myOrangeMoney be shared with my employer?&quot;
                        &gt;
                            &lt;div&gt;
                                The numerical data you enter into myOrangeMoney, including any outside account
                                information, will not be shared with your employer in its original form. Voya will use
                                the data you enter, such as the age at which you’ll retire and your other retirement
                                savings and income, both to estimate your monthly retirement income and to calculate
                                your personalized “replacement income” (RI) score. See below for an explanation of the
                                RI score. Your calculated RI score will be shared with your employer to help your
                                employer assist all of its employees with retirement readiness.
                            &lt;/div&gt;
                        &lt;/voya-expand-collapse&gt;
                    &lt;/li&gt;
                    &lt;li&gt;
                        &lt;voya-expand-collapse heading-text=&quot;What is an RI score?&quot;&gt;
                            &lt;div&gt;
                                Your RI score is a number between 1 and 100 that is derived from a series of
                                calculations based on your age, salary, deferral rate, retirement plan account balance,
                                any outside assets you enter into myOrangeMoney, and other publicly available
                                information. The underlying assumptions are proprietary to Voya and will not be shared
                                with your employer.
                            &lt;/div&gt;
                        &lt;/voya-expand-collapse&gt;
                    &lt;/li&gt;

                    &lt;li&gt;
                        &lt;voya-expand-collapse
                            heading-text=&quot;How will Voya use and secure the data I enter into myOrangeMoney&#174;?&quot;
                        &gt;
                            &lt;div&gt;
                                Voya is committed to protecting the privacy and confidentiality of your personal
                                information. All information entered into myOrangeMoney will be subject to the Voya
                                Financial Privacy Notice. Review the
                                &lt;a
                                    href=&quot;javascript:popWin(&#39;http://www.voya.com/privacy-notice&#39;,500,742,&#39;yes&#39;,&#39;yes&#39;,&#39;yes&#39;,&#39;yes&#39;,&#39;yes&#39;,&#39;yes&#39;,&#39;PopWin&#39;)&quot;
                                    &gt;Privacy Notice&lt;/a
                                &gt;
                                of the Voya companies offering insurance, securities and related financial products and
                                services in the United States.
                            &lt;/div&gt;
                        &lt;/voya-expand-collapse&gt;
                    &lt;/li&gt;
                    &lt;li&gt;
                        &lt;voya-expand-collapse heading-text=&quot;If I call for assistance, to whom will I be connected?&quot;&gt;
                            &lt;div&gt;
                                You will be directed to a VRA Advisor. They have in-depth knowledge of how to use
                                myOrangeMoney and are familiar with the features of your retirement plan. They can also
                                provide information to help you save more for retirement and make the most of your
                                participation in the plan.
                            &lt;/div&gt;
                        &lt;/voya-expand-collapse&gt;
                    &lt;/li&gt;
                    &lt;li&gt;
                        &lt;voya-expand-collapse heading-text=&quot;Will the data I enter into myOrangeMoney be saved?&quot;&gt;
                            &lt;div&gt;
                                There are a few places within the myOrangeMoney experience where you can save your data
                                so it is available upon your return visit. This includes updates made to your
                                &quot;Pension/Other Retirement Savings and Income&quot; field and some fields in &quot;About Me,&quot;
                                excluding date of birth, and pay frequency.
                                &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
                                Any changes to the sliders may also be saved for your return visit. Please refer to “How
                                do the sliders work?” section to learn more.
                            &lt;/div&gt;
                        &lt;/voya-expand-collapse&gt;
                    &lt;/li&gt;
                &lt;/ol&gt;
            &lt;/voya-expand-collapse&gt;
            &lt;voya-expand-collapse heading-text=&quot;Key information used in your analysis:&quot;&gt;
                &lt;div style=&quot;overflow:auto!important;-webkit-overflow-scrolling:touch!important;height:500px;&quot;&gt;
                    &lt;iframe
                        style=&quot;overflow:scroll;-webkit-overflow-scrolling:touch;display:block;height:100%;&quot;
                        width=&quot;100%&quot;
                        height=&quot;100%&quot;
                        frameborder=&quot;0&quot;
                        scrolling=&quot;yes&quot;
                        src=&quot;FE_HDTW_KINFO_URL&quot;
                        title=&quot;Key information used for your analysis&quot;
                        &gt;Key information used for your analysis.&lt;/iframe
                    &gt;
                &lt;/div&gt;
            &lt;/voya-expand-collapse&gt;
            &lt;voya-expand-collapse heading-text=&quot;How are myOrangeMoney income goal estimates calculated?&quot;&gt;
                &lt;ol id=&quot;faq-sections-inner&quot; class=&quot;no-ol-numbering&quot;&gt;
                    &lt;li&gt;
                        &lt;voya-expand-collapse heading-text=&quot;How is my retirement income goal determined?&quot;&gt;
                            &lt;div&gt;
                                Unless otherwise set by you, your estimated retirement income goal is assumed to be 70%
                                of your estimated income at your retirement age. Your retirement income goal is
                                expressed in today&#39;s dollars.
                                &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
                                We estimate your income at retirement age by growing your current salary and your
                                spouse/partner&#39;s salary, (if applicable), by 3.75% annually (or by a percentage
                                otherwise set by you) and adjusting for inflation. Expected inflation averages about
                                3.5% per year, so we subtract 3.5% from your estimated annual income growth. For
                                example, if your estimated annual income growth is 5%, your estimated income increase
                                would be 1.5% per year when adjusted for inflation.
                                &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
                                You are always able to change your salary growth rate assumption by clicking on “About
                                me” or by accessing advisory services online or by speaking with a Voya Retirement
                                Advisor Investment Advisor Representative (VRA Advisor). Keep in mind that Social
                                Security benefits are impacted by any changes, and savings amounts, if set as a
                                percentage of your pay, will be impacted by the salary growth rate as well.
                            &lt;/div&gt;
                        &lt;/voya-expand-collapse&gt;
                    &lt;/li&gt;
                    &lt;li&gt;
                        &lt;voya-expand-collapse
                            heading-text=&quot;Why isn&#39;t my retirement income goal set at 100% of my pre-tax pay?&quot;
                        &gt;
                            &lt;div&gt;
                                Because your expenses may change when you stop working, 100% of your pre-retirement
                                income may not be required to maintain your standard of living in retirement. For
                                instance, some expenses may go down or go away, such as taxes and work-related expenses,
                                while some may go up, like health care costs and money you spend on new hobbies or
                                activities. Some examples of expenses that typically go down are:
                                &lt;ul class=&quot;bulletList&quot;&gt;
                                    &lt;li class=&quot;first&quot;&gt;
                                        Social Security and Medicare tax (FICA). This currently accounts for 7.65% of
                                        annual pay for most people.
                                    &lt;/li&gt;
                                    &lt;li&gt;
                                        Annual Savings for Retirement are no longer needed. Depending on your savings
                                        rate and pay, this could equate to 14% of annual pay.
                                    &lt;/li&gt;
                                    &lt;li&gt;
                                        As most people are generally in lower tax brackets after they retire, the amount
                                        you pay in taxes may go down.
                                    &lt;/li&gt;
                                    &lt;li&gt;
                                        Living expenses and spending habits typically drop over the course of a 30 year
                                        retirement* equating to a 5-15% reduction in annual spending. *
                                    &lt;/li&gt;
                                &lt;/ul&gt;
                                *Research shows that individuals&#39; consumption gradually drops over the course of a 30
                                year retirement, even though health care costs typically increase as a percent of
                                overall consumption.
                            &lt;/div&gt;
                        &lt;/voya-expand-collapse&gt;
                    &lt;/li&gt;
                    &lt;li&gt;
                        &lt;voya-expand-collapse
                            heading-text=&quot;Where do you get my pay to determine my retirement income goal?&quot;
                        &gt;
                            &lt;div&gt;
                                myOrangeMoney typically uses the compensation amount provided by you or your employer.
                                If you or your employer has not provided us with a compensation figure, or if you would
                                like to revise the amount provided, you can do so by clicking on “About me”, accessing
                                advisory services online or by speaking with a VRA Advisor. Please note that if you
                                choose to manually change your salary information, it will be saved and used in your
                                projections. It will be your responsibility to keep this information current as your
                                salary data will no longer be automatically updated by your employer.
                            &lt;/div&gt;
                        &lt;/voya-expand-collapse&gt;
                    &lt;/li&gt;
                    &lt;li&gt;
                        &lt;voya-expand-collapse
                            heading-text=&quot;Can I use myOrangeMoney if I retire or no longer have an income?&quot;
                        &gt;
                            &lt;div&gt;
                                No. This tool is designed to calculate your retirement income goal based on a percent of
                                current income. Without a current income, the tool will use any previous goals set, the
                                previous salary on file to calculate the goal, or use a default goal of $5000. You can
                                still use the advisory services online to make updates or speak with a VRA Advisor who
                                can assist you in evaluating your retirement income needs and your progress towards
                                meeting your goals.
                            &lt;/div&gt;
                        &lt;/voya-expand-collapse&gt;
                    &lt;/li&gt;
                &lt;/ol&gt;
            &lt;/voya-expand-collapse&gt;
            &lt;voya-expand-collapse heading-text=&quot;General Questions&quot;&gt;
                &lt;ol id=&quot;faq-sections-inner&quot; class=&quot;no-ol-numbering&quot;&gt;
                    &lt;li&gt;
                        &lt;voya-expand-collapse heading-text=&#39;Why do you want to know how I &quot;feel&quot; about retirement?&#39;&gt;
                            &lt;div&gt;
                                How you feel about retirement is important because it generally reflects how comfortable
                                you are with your retirement planning. Our goal is to make sure you know where you stand
                                regarding your readiness to retire at every point in your career, and to provide you
                                with the tools that may improve your retirement outlook. We believe having this
                                knowledge and these tools at your disposal can help you feel more in control of your
                                retirement planning and more confident about your financial future.
                            &lt;/div&gt;
                        &lt;/voya-expand-collapse&gt;
                    &lt;/li&gt;
                    &lt;li&gt;
                        &lt;voya-expand-collapse
                            heading-text=&quot;What is the Organize my $$$ feature and how can it help me prepare for retirement?&quot;
                        &gt;
                            &lt;div&gt;
                                This feature is not available to all clients. No matter how close or far away your
                                retirement is, how much you can save for it will be dependent to some extent on your
                                current financial situation. &quot;Organize my $$$&quot; lays out multiple aspects of your
                                financial picture, even including household data, in a digital &quot;Personal Financial
                                Dashboard&quot;, which enables you to monitor a consolidated picture of your overall
                                financial health in one multi-view status report. The &quot;Organize My $$$&quot; dashboard is a
                                component of a holistic planning process that can help you explore your savings options
                                and design and manage your plan, as well as providing access to recommendations that are
                                tailored to fit your particular needs and goals. Please note myOrangeMoney is separate
                                from “Organize my $$$”. As a result, the information you enter under “Organize my $$$”
                                will not carry over to myOrangeMoney.
                            &lt;/div&gt;
                        &lt;/voya-expand-collapse&gt;
                    &lt;/li&gt;
                    &lt;li&gt;
                        &lt;voya-expand-collapse
                            heading-text=&quot;What if I have multiple plans with the same employer on your system?&quot;
                        &gt;
                            &lt;div&gt;
                                In the majority of cases, all plans under the same employer on Voya’s recordkeeping
                                system will be included in your myOrangeMoney estimate. Please review the “Key
                                information used for your analysis” to see what’s included in your forecast. You may add
                                information on any omitted plans by using the advisory services online or by speaking
                                with a VRA Advisor.
                            &lt;/div&gt;
                        &lt;/voya-expand-collapse&gt;
                    &lt;/li&gt;
                    &lt;li&gt;
                        &lt;voya-expand-collapse
                            heading-text=&quot;What if I have two Voya plans from different employers on your system?&quot;
                        &gt;
                            &lt;div&gt;
                                Only the plan or plans under each individual employer will be included in your
                                myOrangeMoney estimates unless you’ve added those other employer accounts by accessing
                                advisory services online or by speaking with an Advisor. To view myOrangeMoney estimates
                                for another employer’s plan on Voya’s recordkeeping system, you will need to log into
                                the plan website for that employer. You also could choose to enter the information for
                                the other employer’s plan by accessing advisory services online or by speaking with a
                                VRA Advisor.
                            &lt;/div&gt;
                        &lt;/voya-expand-collapse&gt;
                    &lt;/li&gt;
                    &lt;li&gt;
                        &lt;voya-expand-collapse heading-text=&quot;How do the contribution sliders work?&quot;&gt;
                            &lt;div&gt;
                                If Voya manages contribution changes for your plan the contribution slider will reflect
                                the current total contribution amount or paycheck deduction that is on file with us. The
                                maximum value on the slider is determined by your Plan&#39;s contribution limit, and the
                                available values on the slider will be in dollars and/or percent depending on your
                                Plan&#39;s rules.
                                &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
                                To see your contribution details for each contribution source, you can expand the View
                                Contributions link. After you have moved the slider, you can click on the button labeled
                                ‘Show me the impact’ to see how your changes will impact your monthly income estimate.
                                You can then accept your changes by clicking on Make Change Now. If you prefer, you can
                                also use the Change Contribution menu to change the amounts for any one or combination
                                of sources.
                                &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
                                If Voya does not manage contributions from your pay for your plan, you will not see a
                                contribution slider. You can submit your contribution changes directly with your
                                employer.
                            &lt;/div&gt;
                        &lt;/voya-expand-collapse&gt;
                    &lt;/li&gt;
                &lt;/ol&gt;
            &lt;/voya-expand-collapse&gt;
            &lt;voya-expand-collapse heading-text=&quot;Estimated Retirement Income in myOrangeMoney&quot;&gt;
                &lt;ol id=&quot;faq-sections-inner&quot; class=&quot;no-ol-numbering&quot;&gt;
                    &lt;li&gt;
                        &lt;voya-expand-collapse heading-text=&quot;How do we forecast retirement income?&quot;&gt;
                            &lt;div&gt;
                                &lt;b&gt;IMPORTANT:&lt;/b&gt; Any forecasts, projected outcomes or other information generated
                                regarding the likelihood of various investment outcomes are hypothetical in nature, do
                                not reflect actual investment results and are not guarantees of future results. In
                                addition, results may vary each time a forecast is generated for you. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
                                &lt;b&gt;Investment Choices:&lt;/b&gt; Your investment choices have been designated by you or your
                                employer, a plan or its representatives, and not by Financial Engines Advisors L.L.C. or
                                Voya Retirement Advisors. Be sure to obtain a current prospectus for any mutual fund
                                investment choices available to you. A prospectus will contain information about the
                                risks, charges, and expenses of the mutual fund. Read and consider it carefully before
                                investing. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
                                &lt;b&gt;Investment Analysis Methods:&lt;/b&gt; Any forecasts presented are not a guarantee of
                                future results, but only reasonable estimates. Forecasts are based upon information
                                about you and your current accounts and investments that we know about, estimated annual
                                savings amount and forward-looking models of the economy and securities markets that
                                utilize data such as historical returns, historical correlations, expected growth rates,
                                and calculated risk premiums. Since past performance is not an accurate predictor of the
                                future and reliance on historical and current data necessarily involves inherent
                                limitations, you must understand that the estimates are only a tool to be used in
                                evaluating your retirement portfolio. Forecast amounts are in today&#39;s dollars, which
                                means that they have been adjusted for inflation. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
                                Forecasts are created by generating thousands of hypothetical future economic scenarios
                                to evaluate how an investment portfolio might perform under a variety of circumstances,
                                including changing interest rates, inflation, and market conditions.
                                &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
                                &lt;b&gt;About Your Information:&lt;/b&gt; If your portfolio includes an account or your other
                                income includes a benefit that may not be fully funded (e.g., a non-qualified deferred
                                compensation plan or a pension plan), we do not provide an assessment of the risk or
                                degree of underfunding. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
                                If your portfolio includes assets invested in a self-directed brokerage option or
                                account, you need to enter that information directly through Online Advice and identify
                                the underlying investments. Alternatively you can speak with a VRA Advisor who can input
                                those details for you. You can reach a VRA Advisor through your plan’s toll free number.
                                Once the account has been entered via Online Advice or a VRA Advisor, you will see it
                                reflected in your myOrangeMoney monthly income estimates.
                                &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
                                If you own investments that you or your employer did not tell us about or that we were
                                unable to model, we do not analyze those investments and they are not included in the
                                analysis. If you are relying on a generic fund to represent an asset that we are unable
                                to model (i.e. private stocks or funds, ETFs, closed-end funds, etc.), that fund is
                                included in our analysis but is not a perfect substitute for your actual investment.
                                Loan balances (if any) are not included in your total account balance or our analysis.
                                &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
                                While we will attempt to update security prices daily and monitor your investments for
                                the various corporate actions that may occur (i.e. splits, mergers), it is ultimately
                                your responsibility to inform us of any changes to your investments. We rely on
                                information provided by you as well as information we have from your plan sponsor to
                                create your forecast. If you have provided spouse or partner information, we rely on
                                that information as well. If you wish to learn about the assumptions we used or to
                                confirm that your information is accurate, please call your plan’s toll free number and
                                ask to speak with a VRA Advisor. We make no representations as to the accuracy or
                                timeliness of the data. The information and the analysis may change over time; we assume
                                no duty to update. Any analysis is provided for educational purposes only and not for
                                the purpose of providing investment advice.
                                &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
                                Investments with “**” in the “Key information used for your analysis” denote the
                                investments and their balances were not recognized and are not included in your account
                                balance, portfolio balance or your retirement forecast.
                                &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
                                &lt;b&gt;Forecasting Risk Over Time:&lt;/b&gt; If you hold a fund whose investment objective
                                includes reducing risk over time (typically referred to as “target date funds”), we
                                model its declining risk according to its stated timeframe. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
                                &lt;u&gt; If you are not currently a member of the Professional Management program&lt;/u&gt;
                                &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
                                For other investments, we assume you maintain a constant investment mix through time; it
                                may be appropriate for you to reduce your investment risk as you approach retirement,
                                but the service cannot predict your future decisions and therefore assumes a constant
                                mix of those investments. In general, if you hold any investments that cannot be
                                reallocated by you, we model those investments on a “buy and hold” basis, rather than
                                assuming that you will adjust their proportions over time.
                                &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
                                &lt;u&gt;If you are enrolled in the Professional Management program&lt;/u&gt;
                                &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
                                The estimated value of your investments assumes participation in the Professional
                                Management program until retirement and also includes any additional investments you or
                                your employer may have told us about and any employer contribution. Forecast amounts
                                reflect the planned adjustments to your risk level as you get closer to retirement.
                                These amounts assume the deduction of the appropriate annual program fees. Any change or
                                elimination of the employer contribution may affect your forecast estimate.
                            &lt;/div&gt;&lt;/voya-expand-collapse
                        &gt;
                    &lt;/li&gt;

                    &lt;li&gt;
                        &lt;voya-expand-collapse heading-text=&quot;How are my paycheck contributions incorporated?&quot;&gt;
                            &lt;div&gt;
                                To estimate annual contributions made by you or your employer to your accounts displayed
                                here, we rely on contributions made by you that we know about, employer contribution
                                rules set up for you or told to us by you and, for contributions tied to your salary,
                                your salary that we know about. We recommend you review and update your salary annually.
                                &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
                                The estimated contribution amounts will include any savings transactions that you have
                                requested and are pending. Please remember that your estimated retirement income
                                forecast may change if the requested savings transactions that are pending are not
                                executed successfully. If you are exploring an alternate value in myOrangeMoney by
                                clicking “Show me the impact,” the new value will be used to provide an estimated
                                retirement income forecast for the hypothetical scenario only as described in more
                                detail under “Interactive Sliders” below.
                                &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
                                For contributions to accounts set up for you, we apply current plan limits and rules as
                                directed by your employer, and, when applicable, current IRS limits to each account
                                individually. Sometimes Voya does not have information relative to plan limits or rules
                                for an account set up for you. In that case, we may rely on you to enter contribution
                                values that comply with the plan limits and rules. We have also included contributions
                                that you told us about to accounts set up by you and, when applicable, applied current
                                IRS limits to each account individually.
                                &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
                                In some cases, IRS limits may apply collectively across accounts. We do not apply IRS
                                limits collectively across accounts. If contributions to your accounts exceed a
                                collective limit, your estimated savings amount may be overstated. As a result, your
                                portfolio and retirement income estimates may also be overstated.
                                &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
                                Additional considerations:
                                &lt;ul class=&quot;bulletList&quot;&gt;
                                    &lt;li class=&quot;first&quot;&gt;
                                        If your plan is subject to contribution limits imposed under Puerto Rico law, we
                                        consider those limits as well.
                                    &lt;/li&gt;
                                    &lt;li&gt;
                                        We take into consideration any plan rule that we know about that allows your
                                        pre-tax (and Roth, if applicable) contributions to continue, for example, as age
                                        50+ catch-up contributions or after-tax contributions once those contributions
                                        reach the IRS limit for the year.
                                    &lt;/li&gt;
                                    &lt;li&gt;
                                        If you participate in an automatic savings program, future increases to your
                                        contributions are not considered.
                                    &lt;/li&gt;
                                &lt;/ul&gt;
                                Current pay and contribution amounts used to calculate your income estimate, in
                                myOrangeMoney, are limited based on laws that govern retirement plans, such as how much
                                money can be contributed annually on a before-tax basis. The maximum annual pay that may
                                be considered in the tool is also constrained by compensation limits that are set
                                annually by the IRS, [(IRC Section 401(a)(17)]. Amounts in excess of the IRC limits are
                                not considered in myOrangeMoney when determining how much you can defer as a percent of
                                salary each year. For example, if the current IRC limit is $270,000 and your pay is
                                $300,000, only the first $270,000 of your pay would be considered as a basis for
                                contributions. So, in this scenario, if your stated contribution were 6 % of annual pay,
                                the deferral amount would be $16,200 per year, not $18,000.
                                &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
                                &lt;b&gt;Contributions are assumed to Continue:&lt;/b&gt; When we estimate your retirement income
                                values and portfolio values, we generally assume contributions (if any) continue until
                                retirement. Sometimes a plan rule may call for employer contributions to cease or change
                                on a specified future date. If we know about that plan rule, we take that into
                                consideration when estimating your retirement income values. If you have specified
                                contributions to an account that are dependent upon a salary from a job with a future
                                start date, your forecasts assume that those contributions start on the specified date.
                                Any changes in employer contributions may affect your forecast estimate.
                                &lt;b&gt;Contributions to an Account with a $0 Balance:&lt;/b&gt; When we estimate your retirement
                                income values and portfolio values, contributions, if any, to an account with a $0
                                balance are not included.
                            &lt;/div&gt;
                        &lt;/voya-expand-collapse&gt;
                    &lt;/li&gt;
                    &lt;li&gt;
                        &lt;voya-expand-collapse heading-text=&quot;Can I model catchup contribution if I’m under 50?&quot;&gt;
                            &lt;div&gt;
                                Catchup contributions can only be modeled if you are currently eligible to make them or
                                will be eligible to make them in the current calendar year. If you are currently under
                                50 and will not be eligible to make catchup contributions in the current calendar year
                                but plan to make catchup contributions in the future, your income estimate may be
                                understated.
                            &lt;/div&gt;
                        &lt;/voya-expand-collapse&gt;
                    &lt;/li&gt;
                    &lt;li&gt;
                        &lt;voya-expand-collapse
                            heading-text=&quot;How does myOrangeMoney handle after-tax contributions (e.g. if I&#39;m contributing to a Roth 401k)?&quot;
                        &gt;
                            &lt;div&gt;
                                If you have an account with an after-tax basis (e.g., 401(k) account to which you make
                                after-tax contributions), that basis is taken into consideration when creating the
                                pre-tax value of your annual retirement income. Starting with your current basis as
                                given by you or we have on file and then adding your projected future after-tax
                                contributions, the estimate will gross up that value to convert to a pre-tax dollar
                                value to express your retirement income forecast in pre-tax dollars. We do the same for
                                any taxable accounts and any basis attributable to Roth contributions and earnings
                                thereon.
                            &lt;/div&gt;
                        &lt;/voya-expand-collapse&gt;
                    &lt;/li&gt;
                    &lt;li&gt;
                        &lt;voya-expand-collapse
                            heading-text=&quot;What if I am planning on other sources of income in retirement?&quot;
                        &gt;
                            &lt;div&gt;
                                You can include other planned sources of income like future pension benefits in
                                retirement by using the &quot;Other Retirement Savings and Income&quot; feature located in the
                                “Let’s talk about” menu. The income you identify will be represented in the estimate of
                                progress towards your retirement income goal.
                                &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
                                &lt;b&gt;Your Other Retirement Assets:&lt;/b&gt;
                                &lt;br /&gt;&lt;be /&gt;
                                We take into account the other retirement assets we know about as shown on the
                                “Retirement Accounts” tab of the &quot;Other Retirement Savings and Income&quot; feature located
                                in the “Let’s talk about” menu and in the “Key information used for your analysis” box.
                                You can include additional retirement accounts by using the advisory services online or
                                by speaking with a VRA Advisor. We assume any assets not managed by us are to be
                                allocated as they are today.
                                &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
                                If you have previously entered other retirement savings and income by using the advisory
                                services online or by speaking with a VRA Advisor, those values will be automatically
                                included in your myOrangeMoney estimates.
                            &lt;/div&gt;
                        &lt;/voya-expand-collapse&gt;
                    &lt;/li&gt;
                    &lt;li&gt;
                        &lt;voya-expand-collapse
                            heading-text=&quot;How is Social Security and Pension Income incorporated into the illustration?&quot;
                        &gt;
                            &lt;div&gt;
                                &lt;b&gt;Information on your pension estimate(s):&lt;/b&gt; Your retirement income forecast includes
                                any pension estimate you have told us about. It may also include a pension estimate we
                                have for you. In that case, if you are actively accruing a benefit we’ll include the
                                pension estimate we received for your retirement age, if available. Otherwise, we’ll
                                include the estimate for the retirement age closest to but not greater than your
                                retirement age or, if not available, an accrued pension estimate. In these cases, we’ll
                                assume the benefit starts at the later of (1) the start age specified for that estimate,
                                or (2) your retirement age. If we have no estimate for an earlier retirement age and no
                                accrued pension estimate, no pension estimate will be included. Whenever we do not have
                                a pension estimate corresponding to your selected retirement age, your forecast may be
                                understated. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
                                We assume that pension estimates entered by you through myOrangeMoney are in future
                                dollars and not protected against inflation. If all or part of your benefit is subject
                                to an annual cost-of-living increase, your forecast may be understated.
                                &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
                                Please refer to the “Key information used for your analysis” on what pension estimates
                                we’ve included or for more information, please go to the advisory services online or by
                                speaking with a VRA Advisor.
                                &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
                                &lt;b&gt;Information on your Social Security estimate(s):&lt;/b&gt; Your Social Security benefit is
                                based on your assumed retirement age. If your Social Security benefit was personalized,
                                we assume values based on your personalization. If your Social Security benefit was
                                estimated by us, we assume you work the required number of years to receive full
                                benefits. Your estimate is in today&#39;s dollars and is not a guarantee. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
                                If you have entered partner/spousal information via the advisory services online or by
                                speaking with a VRA Advisor, their Social Security benefit is based on his or her salary
                                and retirement age. If your partner’s / spouse’s Social Security benefit was
                                personalized, we assume values based on that personalization. If your partner’s/spouse’s
                                Social Security benefit was estimated by us, we assume he or she works the required
                                number of years to receive full benefits. Your partner’s/spouse’s estimate is in today&#39;s
                                dollars and is not a guarantee. We also incorporate their spousal benefits when
                                applicable. &lt;br / &gt;&lt;br /&gt;
                                To create a consistent retirement income in today&#39;s dollars, any benefit specified in
                                future dollars is converted to today&#39;s dollars and any benefit specified to start at an
                                age other than your planned retirement age is &quot;smoothed&quot; over the retirement years. That
                                is, benefits specified to start after your stated retirement age are reduced in the
                                retirement income estimate to account for the retirement years for which the benefit is
                                not yet in effect. Alternatively, benefits specified to start before your retirement are
                                increased in the annual income estimate to reflect the opportunity for additional
                                savings in the pre-retirement years.
                                &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
                                &lt;b&gt;What if I may be subject to the Windfall Elimination Provision (WEP)?:&lt;/b&gt; The
                                Windfall Elimination Provision (WEP) affects how the amount of your retirement benefit
                                is calculated if you receive a pension from work where Social Security taxes were not
                                taken out of your pay. According to the Social Security Administration, if you work for
                                an employer who does not withhold Social Security taxes from your salary, any pension
                                you get based on that work may reduce your Social Security benefits. A modified formula
                                is used to calculate your benefit amount, resulting in a lower Social Security benefit
                                than you otherwise would receive. If you are subject to the WEP, you can use the
                                &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.ssa.gov/planners/retire/anyPiaWepjs04.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;
                                    WEP calculator on the Social Security website&lt;/a
                                &gt;
                                to estimate your benefit payments. Enter the monthly retirement benefit estimate from
                                the WEP calculator by accessing advisory services online or by speaking with a VRA
                                Advisor. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
                                Retirement income sources such as pension or Social Security benefits are estimates and
                                not guaranteed.
                            &lt;/div&gt;
                        &lt;/voya-expand-collapse&gt;
                    &lt;/li&gt;
                    &lt;li&gt;
                        &lt;voya-expand-collapse
                            heading-text=&quot;Do you include my retirement plan account stock options in the retirement income estimate?&quot;
                        &gt;
                            &lt;div&gt;
                                If you have stock options available from your employer and they are associated with your
                                retirement goal, please refer to the “Key information used for your analysis” to see
                                what’s included. To learn more about how we may include information about your stock
                                options in your forecast, please go to the advisory services online or speak with a VRA
                                Advisor.
                            &lt;/div&gt;
                        &lt;/voya-expand-collapse&gt;
                    &lt;/li&gt;
                    &lt;li&gt;
                        &lt;voya-expand-collapse
                            heading-text=&quot;How is my estimated monthly income calculated in myOrangeMoney?&quot;
                        &gt;
                            &lt;div&gt;
                                The income you have available in your retirement will be based on income from your
                                investments, Social Security, Railroad Retirement, and any pension or other forms of
                                retirement income we may know about. To see the detailed assumptions used, please refer
                                to the “Key information used for your analysis” above.
                                &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
                                If you have provided spouse/partner information, your retirement income estimate
                                considers both of you. The estimate assumes that the surviving household member receives
                                50% of the annual income amount.
                                &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
                                &lt;u&gt;Income from investments&lt;/u&gt;
                                &lt;br /&gt;
                                To estimate your retirement income from investments, we use a process called
                                annuitization and adjust for inflation to translate estimated portfolio values at
                                retirement age into annual pre-tax estimated retirement incomes in today&#39;s dollars.
                                &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
                                Your monthly income forecast for average market performance as shown in “Key information
                                used for your analysis” represents the 50th percentile of thousands of hypothetical
                                future economic scenarios. There is a 50% chance that you will have at least the monthly
                                income forecasted in retirement. Your monthly income forecast for poor market
                                performance as shown in “Key information used for your analysis” represents the 5th
                                percentile of thousands of hypothetical future economic scenarios. There is a 5% chance
                                that you will have the monthly income forecasted or less in retirement. If you are
                                enrolled in the Professional Management program, these amounts assume the deduction of
                                the appropriate annual program fees.
                                &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
                                If you have an account with an after-tax basis (e.g., 401(k) account to which you make
                                after-tax contributions) we take that basis into consideration when creating the pre-tax
                                value of your annual retirement income. We start with your current basis we have on
                                record for you and then add your projected future after-tax contributions. We then gross
                                up that value to convert to a pre-tax dollar value to express your retirement income
                                forecast in pre-tax dollars. We do the same for any taxable accounts and any basis
                                attributable to Roth contributions and earnings thereon.
                                &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
                                Any forecasts, projected outcomes or other information generated regarding the
                                likelihood of various investment outcomes are hypothetical in nature, do not reflect
                                actual investment results and are not guarantees of future results.
                                &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
                                If your retirement age, your contribution rate, or your employer contribution changes,
                                your forecasts may differ.
                                &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
                                &lt;u&gt;For individuals enrolled in the Professional Management program&lt;/u&gt;
                                &lt;br /&gt;
                                Although we take into account the additional investment information you have told us
                                about to create your forecast, we may not manage your other accounts.
                                &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
                                Income from Social Security and Pensions
                                &lt;br /&gt;
                                Refer to the section “How is Social Security and Pension Income incorporated into the
                                illustration?” for information on how this is included.
                                &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
                                &lt;b&gt;Taxes:&lt;/b&gt; U.S. federal and state tax rates and regulations are used to generate your
                                forecast. We assume that the amount of your income taxed by your state is the same as
                                your taxable income for federal income tax purposes. If we were not provided a U.S. tax
                                state because you have an overseas military address, we assume a state marginal tax rate
                                of 0.00% unless changed by you. If your tax state is Puerto Rico, we assume no federal
                                taxes and rely upon Puerto Rico tax rates.
                            &lt;/div&gt;
                        &lt;/voya-expand-collapse&gt;
                    &lt;/li&gt;
                &lt;/ol&gt;
            &lt;/voya-expand-collapse&gt;
            &lt;voya-expand-collapse heading-text=&quot;Interactive Sliders and Data Input in myOrangeMoney&quot;&gt;
                &lt;ol id=&quot;faq-sections-inner&quot; class=&quot;no-ol-numbering&quot;&gt;
                    &lt;li&gt;
                        &lt;voya-expand-collapse heading-text=&quot;How do the sliders work?&quot;&gt;
                            &lt;div&gt;
                                If present, you can use the sliders to experiment with the effect on your forecast if
                                you make changes to your retirement age or an annual contribution to an account. In
                                order to save any new slider value, you will need to first click the “Show me the
                                impact” button to get a revised forecast with the new value(s). Then you can click the
                                “Make Change Now” button, to validate. Once validated, click “I like it, let’s do it” to
                                request an update. A Retirement Age change will be reflected immediately. A contribution
                                change will become a pending savings transaction until it’s executed successfully, which
                                may take one to two payroll cycles. Pending savings transactions are reflected in your
                                estimated retirement income forecasts. Please remember that your estimated retirement
                                income forecast may change if the requested savings transactions that are pending are
                                not executed successfully. If you are exploring an alternate value in myOrangeMoney by
                                clicking “Show me the impact,” any new value will be used to provide an estimated
                                retirement income forecast for the hypothetical scenario but is not saved.

                                &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
                                Please note that saving new contribution values are done at the account level and will
                                need to be done one at a time for each account for which you’d like a contribution
                                change saved.
                                &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
                                &lt;b&gt;The Retirement Age slider:&lt;/b&gt; We use your Retirement Age to determine how long your
                                investments can grow and when you might start to draw on those investments. We model
                                your contributions and investment growth until your Retirement Age. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
                                Moving the slider: If you are not currently a member of Professional Management, you may
                                move the slider to see how your forecast changes if you change your Retirement Age.
                                &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
                                Choosing your Retirement Age: Retiring later typically improves your forecast because
                                you have more years to accumulate savings and investments and fewer years of retirement
                                to be funded. Retiring earlier may have the opposite effect.
                                &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
                                For current members of Professional Management, the Retirement Age shown is your
                                selected or defaulted Retirement Age. To make changes, please go to the Professional
                                Management member site or call an advisor representative to discuss the impact on your
                                retirement outlook.
                                &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
                                &lt;b&gt;The Contribution slider: &lt;/b&gt;
                                &lt;br /&gt;
                                Moving the slider: Move the slider and click on “Show me the impact” to see how your
                                forecast changes if you contribute more or less to a specified account. As you move the
                                slider to change your contribution amount, please see the information below the slider
                                for a breakdown of the amount by contribution type. Saving any new contribution value
                                will require you to first click the “Show me the impact” button to get a revised
                                forecast with the new value but the new value is not saved. Then you can click the “Make
                                Change Now” button, to validate. Once validated, click, “I like it, let’s do it” to
                                request an update. This will become a pending savings transaction until it’s executed
                                successfully, which may take one to two payroll cycles. Pending savings transactions are
                                reflected in your estimated retirement income. Please remember that your estimated
                                retirement income forecast may change if the requested savings transactions that are
                                pending with the provider are not executed successfully. If you are exploring an
                                alternate value in myOrangeMoney by clicking “Show me the impact,” any new value will be
                                used to provide an estimated retirement income forecast for the hypothetical scenario
                                but is not saved.
                                &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
                                Adjusting contributions if you have several accounts: If you have multiple accounts to
                                which you may contribute, select a different account from the drop-down list. Then move
                                the slider to adjust the contribution to that account.
                                &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
                                &lt;b&gt;Important note about adjusting contributions for multiple accounts:&lt;/b&gt; Your forecast
                                estimate will only show the impact of one hypothetical contribution change at a time.
                                Thus, selecting a different account from the drop-down list and clicking “Show me the
                                impact” will reset any other account contributions you’ve adjusted back to the original
                                value or to that of your pending savings transactions and your forecast will no longer
                                include any contribution value you experimented with for a different account.
                                &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
                                Please note that saving new contribution values are done at the account level and will
                                need to be done one at a time for each account for which you’d like a contribution
                                change saved.
                                &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
                                Slider range: For a given account, the contribution limits for that account determine
                                the range of the contributions slider.
                            &lt;/div&gt;
                        &lt;/voya-expand-collapse&gt;
                    &lt;/li&gt;
                    &lt;li&gt;
                        &lt;voya-expand-collapse
                            heading-text=&quot;What is the feature ‘Special Needs planning for you or a loved one’?&quot;
                        &gt;
                            &lt;div&gt;
                                The need for retirement planning expands when you or a loved one has a disability.
                                Understanding what it could mean and preparing early can equal success for you and those
                                dear to you. This feature allows you to model additional benefits at retirement, if
                                applicable. It also allows you to re-evaluate your monthly savings goal at retirement.
                                If you have a disability or may be caring for a loved one with a disability during your
                                retirement, you may need to save more to cover additional expenses.
                            &lt;/div&gt;
                        &lt;/voya-expand-collapse&gt;
                    &lt;/li&gt;

                    &lt;li&gt;
                        &lt;voya-expand-collapse heading-text=&quot;What does the Reset button do?&quot;&gt;
                            &lt;div&gt;
                                The Reset button simply allows you to reset the sliders back to where they were when you
                                entered the session unless you have requested the changes to be saved. This is a
                                convenience feature that enables you to model various scenarios without requesting any
                                actual changes to your account. Using the Reset button, however, will not undo changes
                                you’ve already requested.
                            &lt;/div&gt;
                        &lt;/voya-expand-collapse&gt;
                    &lt;/li&gt;
                    &lt;li&gt;
                        &lt;voya-expand-collapse heading-text=&quot;How do I include my spouse&#39;s income in the goal?&quot;&gt;
                            &lt;div&gt;
                                While myOrangeMoney does not currently allow you to add information for your spouse or
                                partner, you can do so by entering it through the advisory services online or by
                                speaking with a VRA Advisor. Any information entered in that manner will carry forward
                                to future myOrangeMoney sessions.
                            &lt;/div&gt;
                        &lt;/voya-expand-collapse&gt;
                    &lt;/li&gt;
                    &lt;li&gt;
                        &lt;voya-expand-collapse heading-text=&quot;What if I currently have multiple sources of income?&quot;&gt;
                            &lt;div&gt;
                                You can add other sources of current income (for example a second job) through the
                                advisory services online or by speaking with a VRA Advisor. Any information entered in
                                that manner will carry forward to future myOrangeMoney sessions.
                            &lt;/div&gt;
                        &lt;/voya-expand-collapse&gt;
                    &lt;/li&gt;
                &lt;/ol&gt;&lt;/voya-expand-collapse
            &gt;

            &lt;voya-expand-collapse heading-text=&quot;Retirement Health Care&quot;&gt;
                &lt;div class=&quot;ui-faq-accordion-content-visible&quot;&gt;
                    &lt;span
                        &gt;Please note that the Retirement Healthcare feature is separate from your myOrangeMoney
                        retirement income estimate.&lt;/span
                    &gt;
                &lt;/div&gt;
                &lt;ol id=&quot;faq-sections-inner&quot; class=&quot;no-ol-numbering&quot;&gt;
                    &lt;li&gt;
                        &lt;voya-expand-collapse heading-text=&quot;Are retiree health care costs included in my goal?&quot;&gt;
                            &lt;div&gt;
                                The default 70% &quot;replacement income&quot; goal may meet typical expenses in retirement,
                                including health care costs. If you feel your health care costs in retirement will be
                                higher or lower than typical, you can modify your replacement income goal to be more or
                                less than the default value of 70%.
                            &lt;/div&gt;
                        &lt;/voya-expand-collapse&gt;
                    &lt;/li&gt;
                    &lt;li&gt;
                        &lt;voya-expand-collapse heading-text=&quot;Can you explain how the health care modeling works?&quot;&gt;
                            &lt;div&gt;
                                (If applicable), You can also use the Retirement Healthcare feature located in the
                                &quot;Let’s talk about&quot; menu to better estimate your health care expenses in retirement. By
                                confirming the state in which you plan to live in retirement, we can illustrate the
                                potential expenses you would incur at varying five year increments, starting at age 65.
                                The increase in costs is based on an inflation rate of 6.5% annually and is represented
                                in today’s dollars. This will help you to assess whether your retirement income estimate
                                is adequate to meet your needs as you age. If not, you can consider additional savings
                                options. Note that choosing a state here does not affect the myOrangeMoney retirement
                                income forecast. The 6.5% annual inflation rate assumption is only used in the
                                Retirement Healthcare feature – assumptions used for your retirement income forecast may
                                differ.
                            &lt;/div&gt;
                        &lt;/voya-expand-collapse&gt;
                    &lt;/li&gt;
                    &lt;li&gt;
                        &lt;voya-expand-collapse heading-text=&quot;What is Medicare?&quot;&gt;
                            &lt;div&gt;
                                Medicare is our country’s health insurance program for people age 65 or older (Medicare
                                may also cover people under age 65 with certain disabilities and people of any age with
                                End-Stage Renal Disease). Unless you choose a Medicare Advantage Plan from a private
                                insurer (like an HMO or PPO), you may be entitled to benefits managed by the Federal
                                government including Medicare Part A benefits. You may also elect to purchase Medicare
                                Part B benefits, Part D or prescription drug coverage or Medicare Supplemental Coverage,
                                also referred to as Medigap Coverage. You may experience some additional healthcare
                                related costs not covered by any of these Medicare benefits. Costs associated with Long
                                Term Care needs are not addressed by this experience or estimate. All costs are in
                                current dollars. If you retire before you are eligible for Medicare you may choose to
                                purchase private health insurance or to self-insure. Costs and coverage for private
                                health insurance varies greatly and are not estimated with this tool.
                                &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
                                Different parts of Medicare cover different services. The main parts of Medicare are
                                further summarized below.
                                &lt;ul class=&quot;bulletList&quot;&gt;
                                    &lt;li class=&quot;first&quot;&gt;
                                        Medicare Part A Hospital Insurance - Most people do not pay a premium in
                                        retirement for Part A if they or a spouse already paid for it through their
                                        payroll taxes while working. Medicare Part A helps cover inpatient care in
                                        hospitals, including critical access hospitals, and skilled nursing facilities
                                        (not custodial or long-term care). It also helps cover hospice care and some
                                        home health care. Beneficiaries must meet certain conditions to get these
                                        benefits. Note also that co-payments, coinsurance or deductibles may apply.
                                    &lt;/li&gt;
                                    &lt;li&gt;
                                        Medicare Part B Medical or Doctor’s Insurance - Most people pay a monthly
                                        premium in retirement for Part B. Medicare Part B helps cover medically
                                        necessary doctors&#39; services and outpatient care. It also covers some other
                                        medical services that Part A doesn&#39;t cover, such as some of the services of
                                        physical and occupational therapists, and some home health care. Part B premiums
                                        are uniform nationally and are increased for those with a higher Modified
                                        Adjusted Gross Income.
                                    &lt;/li&gt;
                                    &lt;li&gt;
                                        Medicare Part C Supplemental premium or Medigap - Medigap or Medicare Part C
                                        coverage is optional and is provided through insurance policies issues by
                                        private insurers (Plans A-N). You may incur out-of-pocket healthcare expenses,
                                        for costs not covered by Medicare benefits and Medigap insurance.
                                    &lt;/li&gt;
                                    &lt;li&gt;
                                        Medicare Part D Prescription Drug coverage - Part D coverage is optional.
                                        Premiums are increased for those with a higher Modified Adjusted Gross Income,
                                        differ from state to state, and vary based on the specific plan and level of
                                        benefit selected. Most people will pay a monthly premium for this coverage.
                                        Everyone with Medicare can get this coverage that may help lower prescription
                                        drug costs and help protect against higher costs in the future. Medicare
                                        Prescription Drug Coverage is insurance. Private companies provide the coverage.
                                        Beneficiaries choose the drug plan and pay a monthly premium. Like other
                                        insurance, if a beneficiary decides not to enroll in a drug plan when they are
                                        first eligible, they may pay a penalty if they choose to join later.
                                    &lt;/li&gt;
                                    &lt;li&gt;
                                        Out-of-Pocket – This is estimated and refers to healthcare costs not covered by
                                        any of the above plans. Examples of possible costs include dental, vision,
                                        hearing aids, medications not covered by Part D, copays, deductibles or other
                                        services not covered by Medigap.
                                    &lt;/li&gt;
                                    &lt;li&gt;
                                        Pre-Medicare Supplemental – I f you retire before age 65, you may need to
                                        purchase private health insurance (or self-insure). Costs and coverage vary
                                        greatly. Pricing for Affordable Care Act eligible plans may be researched at
                                        &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.healthcare.gov&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt; www.healthcare.gov&lt;/a&gt;.
                                        This tool does not provide estimates for private insurance should you choose to
                                        retire before age 65.
                                    &lt;/li&gt;
                                &lt;/ul&gt;
                                &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
                                &lt;b
                                    &gt;Please consult Medicare.gov for a complete description of Medicare. The summary
                                    above was prepared from the publication Medicare and You: found at
                                    &lt;a
                                        href=&quot;https://www.medicare.gov/pubs/pdf/10050-Medicare-and-You.pdf&quot;
                                        target=&quot;_blank&quot;
                                    &gt;
                                        https://www.medicare.gov/pubs/pdf/10050-Medicare-and-You.pdf&lt;/a
                                    &gt;&lt;/b
                                &gt;
                            &lt;/div&gt;
                        &lt;/voya-expand-collapse&gt;
                    &lt;/li&gt;
                    &lt;li&gt;
                        &lt;voya-expand-collapse heading-text=&quot;What is Medicaid?&quot;&gt;
                            &lt;div&gt;
                                If you cannot afford to pay your Medicare premiums and other medical costs, you may be
                                able to get help. Medicaid is a joint federal and state government program that helps
                                low-income retirees cover healthcare expenses. Each state has its own rules about who is
                                eligible and what is covered under Medicaid. Some people qualify for both Medicare and
                                Medicaid. Medicaid covers most basic health services and many costs not covered by
                                Medicare like prescription drugs, nursing home care, eye exams, glasses, and more.
                                Medicaid may also help to pay for Medicare costs. For more information about the
                                Medicaid program, contact your local medical assistance agency, social services or
                                welfare office. The retirement health care tool does not consider whether you will be
                                eligible for Medicaid and estimates Medicare and other retiree health care costs the
                                same way for everyone.
                            &lt;/div&gt;
                        &lt;/voya-expand-collapse&gt;
                    &lt;/li&gt;
                    &lt;li&gt;
                        &lt;voya-expand-collapse heading-text=&quot;What if I already have medical insurance?&quot;&gt;
                            &lt;div&gt;
                                If you already have other health insurance when you become eligible for Medicare, you
                                should consider whether it is worth the monthly premium cost to sign up for Medicare
                                medical insurance. The answer varies with each person and the kind of other health
                                insurance you may have. You should speak with the appropriate resource for your
                                circumstances. If you are still working and covered by your employer group health plan,
                                speak to your personnel or benefits office. If you are not covered under an employer
                                plan, reach out to your advisor or insurance agent for assistance.
                            &lt;/div&gt;
                        &lt;/voya-expand-collapse&gt;
                    &lt;/li&gt;
                &lt;/ol&gt;&lt;/voya-expand-collapse
            &gt;

            &lt;voya-expand-collapse heading-text=&quot;Loan Options in myOrangeMoney&quot;&gt;
                &lt;ol id=&quot;faq-sections-inner&quot; class=&quot;no-ol-numbering&quot;&gt;
                    &lt;li&gt;
                        &lt;voya-expand-collapse heading-text=&quot;When would this feature be available to me?&quot;&gt;
                            &lt;div&gt;
                                If your plan has the myOrangeMoney loan feature enabled, you will be able to select
                                “Let’s talk about your loan options” when you can request a loan or if you have an
                                active loan.
                            &lt;/div&gt;
                        &lt;/voya-expand-collapse&gt;
                    &lt;/li&gt;
                    &lt;li&gt;
                        &lt;voya-expand-collapse
                            heading-text=&quot;When I model taking a new loan, how is the impact to my retirement income calculated?&quot;
                        &gt;
                            &lt;div&gt;
                                The estimated income from the modeled loan amount is subtracted from your current
                                estimated retirement income. By selecting the ? icon next to the &quot;After Loan amount&quot;
                                text, or by selecting the “See the value of repayment link”, you can also see the
                                estimated value of making your scheduled payments.
                                &lt;br /&gt;
                                &lt;br /&gt;The assumption for retirement age is the same as the retirement age used in the
                                retirement savings view of myOrangeMoney. A 6.00% rate of return and a 3.00% annual
                                inflation rate are assumed. These return and inflation assumptions only apply to how we
                                estimate the change to retirement income with respect to loans. For information on how
                                we estimate income from your investments and other retirement sources, see &quot;How do we
                                illustrate retirement income?&quot;
                            &lt;/div&gt;
                        &lt;/voya-expand-collapse&gt;
                    &lt;/li&gt;
                    &lt;li&gt;
                        &lt;voya-expand-collapse heading-text=&quot;How are my outstanding loans treated?&quot;&gt;
                            &lt;div&gt;
                                Your standard retirement income estimate does not assume future loan payments. To see an
                                estimate for the value of making your remaining scheduled loan payments, you can select
                                “Let’s talk about your loan options” and then select “View Details”. The estimated value
                                of future loan payments is labeled “From Future Loan Payments”.
                                &lt;br /&gt;
                                &lt;br /&gt;If you have defaulted on a loan, no additional payments are assumed. Please note
                                that you may incur additional penalties and/or taxes when you default on a loan, those
                                scenarios are not illustrated.
                                &lt;br /&gt;
                                &lt;br /&gt;The assumption for retirement age is the same as the retirement age used in the
                                retirement savings view of myOrangeMoney. A 6.00% rate of return and 3.00% annual
                                inflation rate are assumed. These return and inflation assumptions only apply to how we
                                estimate the change to retirement income with respect to loans. For information on how
                                we estimate income from your investments and other retirement sources, see &quot;How do we
                                illustrate retirement income?&quot;
                            &lt;/div&gt;
                        &lt;/voya-expand-collapse&gt;
                    &lt;/li&gt;
                    &lt;li&gt;
                        &lt;voya-expand-collapse heading-text=&quot;What if I retire before my loan is paid off?&quot;&gt;
                            &lt;div&gt;
                                If your estimated retirement age occurs before your last scheduled loan payment, the
                                estimate assumes that the loan will be repaid in full at the time of retirement.
                            &lt;/div&gt;
                        &lt;/voya-expand-collapse&gt;
                    &lt;/li&gt;
                    &lt;li&gt;
                        &lt;voya-expand-collapse heading-text=&quot;What happens if I don’t make my loan payments?&quot;&gt;
                            &lt;div&gt;
                                You&#39;ll have to pay taxes on the total outstanding loan balance. And you will also need
                                to pay a 10% premature distribution penalty, unless an exception applies, if you&#39;re
                                under age 59&#189;. Any unpaid amount will continue to accrue interest until there is a
                                distributable event and will count against your future loan availability.
                                &lt;br /&gt;
                                &lt;br /&gt;Keep in mind that if you leave your job, you generally have a limited time to pay
                                off the loan. If your plan allows the loan to continue, your payment method may need to
                                change.
                            &lt;/div&gt;
                        &lt;/voya-expand-collapse&gt;
                    &lt;/li&gt;
                &lt;/ol&gt;
            &lt;/voya-expand-collapse&gt;
            &lt;br /&gt;
            &lt;br /&gt;
            &lt;br /&gt;
            CN0315-40811-0420D
            &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
            No representations, warranties or guarantees are made as to the accuracy of any projections or calculations.
            Neither Voya Retirement Insurance and Annuity Company nor Voya Institutional Plan Services, LLC shall be
            liable for any damages or costs of any type arising out of or in any way connected with your use of this
            calculator. This information does not serve, either directly or indirectly, as legal, financial or tax
            advice and you should always consult a qualified professional legal, financial and/or tax advisor when
            making decisions related to your individual tax situation. &#169; 2019 Edelman Financial Engines, LLC. Edelman Financial
            Engines&#174; is a registered trademark of Edelman Financial Engines, LLC. All other marks are the exclusive property of
            their respective owners
            &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;

